The paper discusses the issue of publishing executable computational research results, which involves aspects of computer systems (cs.CY), digital libraries (cs.DL), software engineering (cs.SE), databases (cs.DB), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The focus on reproducibility and transparency also suggests a connection to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper does not explicitly mention network analysis or graph theory, we consider cs.SI less likely than the other categories.
